nd the bonds of love they share across borders. The result is an absorbing and literally moving ethnography that illuminates the mutually reinforcing and constitutive forces that impact the lives of migrants and their loved ones-and how profoundly migrants are underserved by policies that more often lead to their illegality, statelessness, deportation, detention, and abuse than to their aid.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aImmigrantsxFamily relationshipszPersian Gulf States. 0aImmigrantszPersian Gulf StatesxSocial conditions. 0aWomen immigrantsxFamily relationshipszPersian Gulf States. 0aWomen immigrantszPersian Gulf StatesxSocial conditions. 4adeportation. 4adetention. 4afamily. 4agendered migration. 4asexuality. 4astatelessness. 4atrafficking policy. 4azina. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070397940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080479884640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804798846423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804798846.jpg  a978-3-11-070397-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles